Note: ============================================================================
Note: COUNTRY-CODE EXTRACTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse the country code from the leading digits after the '+' sign per
ITU-T E.164. The country code is 1..3 digits; the parser uses longest-
prefix matching against the known dial-code table for codes 2 and 3
digits long, falling back to single-digit codes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Try the first 3 digits as a candidate code.
2. If recognized in phone_region_for_country_code, accept length 3.
3. Otherwise try first 2 digits; same dispatch.
4. Otherwise try first 1 digit; same dispatch.
5. If none recognized: return -1 with no consumed prefix.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) - three table lookups.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 when no code matches so callers know the number cannot be
parsed against the country table.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_detect_country_code" takes digits_str as Integer, start as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    If digits_str is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    If length is less than 1:
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: Try 3 digits.
    If length is greater than or equal to 3:
        Let d0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with digits_str, start
        Let d1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with digits_str, start plus 1
        Let d2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with digits_str, start plus 2
        Let cc3 be ((d0 minus 48) multiplied by 100) plus ((d1 minus 48) multiplied by 10) plus (d2 minus 48)
        Let region3 be proc phone_region_for_country_code with cc3
        If region3 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with region3
            Return cc3
        End If
    End If

    Note: Try 2 digits.
    If length is greater than or equal to 2:
        Let d0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with digits_str, start
        Let d1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with digits_str, start plus 1
        Let cc2 be ((d0 minus 48) multiplied by 10) plus (d1 minus 48)
        Let region2 be proc phone_region_for_country_code with cc2
        If region2 is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with region2
            Return cc2
        End If
    End If

    Note: Try 1 digit.
    Let d0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with digits_str, start
    Let cc1 be d0 minus 48
    Let region1 be proc phone_region_for_country_code with cc1
    If region1 is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with region1
        Return cc1
    End If
    Return -1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RECORD MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "phone_create" returns Integer:
    Let rec be proc allocate from Layout with PHONE_RECORD_SIZE
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 32, PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 40, 0
    Return rec
End Process

Process called "phone_destroy" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nat be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 8
    If nat is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nat
    End If
    Let reg be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 16
    If reg is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with reg
    End If
    Let ext be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 24
    If ext is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with ext
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with rec
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "phone_get_country_code" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 0
End Process

Process called "phone_get_national_number" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 8
End Process

Process called "phone_get_region" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 16
End Process

Process called "phone_get_classification" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 32
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Extract digits from a phone-number string. The input may contain visual
formatting characters: '+', '-', ' ', '(', ')', '.', that are ignored
during digit collection per ITU-T E.123 (Notation for national and
international telephone numbers).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
StringBuilder loop. Append only ASCII digits; ignore the formatting
characters listed above. Any other character aborts the parse.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict on character class: returns 0 if any non-formatting non-digit
character appears.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_extract_digits" takes input_str as Integer, start as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    If input_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    Let failed be 0
    While i is less than length:
        If failed is equal to 0:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, start plus i
            Let is_d be proc is_digit from Char with ch
            If is_d is equal to 1:
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
            Otherwise:
                Let is_format be 0
                If ch is equal to 45:
                    Set is_format to 1
                End If
                If ch is equal to 32:
                    Set is_format to 1
                End If
                If ch is equal to 40:
                    Set is_format to 1
                End If
                If ch is equal to 41:
                    Set is_format to 1
                End If
                If ch is equal to 46:
                    Set is_format to 1
                End If
                If is_format is equal to 0:
                    Set failed to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If failed is equal to 1:
        proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
        Return 0
    End If
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse an E.164 phone number. The input must begin with '+', followed by
1..15 digits with optional formatting characters mixed in. The first
group of digits (per longest-prefix match against the dial-code table)
is the country code; the rest is the national number.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Verify input starts with '+'.
2. Extract all digits from the remainder, dropping formatters.
3. Detect country code via longest-prefix match.
4. Slice national number from the rest of the digit string.
5. Allocate PhoneNumber record and populate country code, national
   number, and region (looked up by country code).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Refuses input without '+', empty digit sequences, country codes not in
the table, and total length outside the 1..15 E.164 bound. Returns 0 on
any failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_from_e164_string" takes input_str as Integer returns Integer:
    If input_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with input_str
    If length is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, 0
    If first is not equal to 43:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let digits be proc phone_extract_digits with input_str, 1, length minus 1
    If digits is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let digit_count be proc string_length from StringCore with digits
    If digit_count is less than PHONE_NATIONAL_MIN_DIGITS plus 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with digits
        Return 0
    End If
    If digit_count is greater than PHONE_E164_MAX_DIGITS:
        proc deallocate from Layout with digits
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cc be proc phone_detect_country_code with digits, 0, digit_count
    If cc is less than 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with digits
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cc_len be 1
    If cc is greater than or equal to 10:
        Set cc_len to 2
    End If
    If cc is greater than or equal to 100:
        Set cc_len to 3
    End If
    Let nat_start be cc_len
    Let nat_len be digit_count minus cc_len
    If nat_len is less than PHONE_NATIONAL_MIN_DIGITS:
        proc deallocate from Layout with digits
        Return 0
    End If
    Let national be proc string_substring from StringPrim with digits, nat_start, nat_len
    proc deallocate from Layout with digits
    If national is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rec be proc phone_create
    If rec is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with national
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 0, cc
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 8, national
    Let region be proc phone_region_for_country_code with cc
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 16, region

    Note: Country-specific classification.
    Let cls be proc phone_classify with cc, national
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 32, cls
    Return rec
End Process

@Reasoning
Build a phone number from explicit country code and national-number
digits. Useful when constructing test fixtures or when receiving data
from a system that already separates the parts.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Validate inputs, copy the national-number string, populate the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over national-number length. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on any validation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_from_national" takes cc as Integer, national_str as Integer returns Integer:
    If cc is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If cc is greater than 999:
        Return 0
    End If
    If national_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nat_len be proc string_length from StringCore with national_str
    If nat_len is less than PHONE_NATIONAL_MIN_DIGITS:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cc_digits be 1
    If cc is greater than or equal to 10:
        Set cc_digits to 2
    End If
    If cc is greater than or equal to 100:
        Set cc_digits to 3
    End If
    If cc_digits plus nat_len is greater than PHONE_E164_MAX_DIGITS:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: National number must be digits only.
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nat_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, i
        Let is_d be proc is_digit from Char with ch
        If is_d is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let national_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with national_str
    If national_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rec be proc phone_create
    If rec is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with national_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 0, cc
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 8, national_copy
    Let region be proc phone_region_for_country_code with cc
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 16, region
    Let cls be proc phone_classify with cc, national_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, 32, cls
    Return rec
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CLASSIFICATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Classify a phone number by country-specific rules. The classification
table here covers the most-common dispatch points needed by application
code (US toll-free recognition, US/UK mobile vs landline) while leaving
unknown numbers marked as PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on country code:
  - US (1): leading area code 800/888/877/866/855/844/833 -> toll-free.
            Other are landline by default at this level of detail
            (mobile/landline overlap heavily in NANP since 2003).
  - UK (44): national starting with '7' -> mobile;
             national starting with '20', '11', '13', '14', '15', '16',
             '17', '18', '19' -> landline;
             national starting with '500', '800', '808', '8001', '8002' ->
             toll-free.
  - Other codes: returns PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input beyond validated digit string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_classify" takes cc as Integer, national_str as Integer returns Integer:
    If national_str is equal to 0:
        Return PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN
    End If
    Let nat_len be proc string_length from StringCore with national_str
    If nat_len is less than 3:
        Return PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN
    End If

    If cc is equal to 1:
        Let d0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 0
        Let d1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 1
        Let d2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 2
        Let area_code be ((d0 minus 48) multiplied by 100) plus ((d1 minus 48) multiplied by 10) plus (d2 minus 48)
        If area_code is equal to 800:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
        End If
        If area_code is equal to 888:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
        End If
        If area_code is equal to 877:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
        End If
        If area_code is equal to 866:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
        End If
        If area_code is equal to 855:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
        End If
        If area_code is equal to 844:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
        End If
        If area_code is equal to 833:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
        End If
        Return PHONE_CLASS_LANDLINE
    End If

    If cc is equal to 44:
        Let d0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 0
        If d0 is equal to 55:
            Return PHONE_CLASS_MOBILE
        End If
        If nat_len is greater than or equal to 2:
            Let d1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 1
            Let prefix2 be ((d0 minus 48) multiplied by 10) plus (d1 minus 48)
            If prefix2 is equal to 20:
                Return PHONE_CLASS_LANDLINE
            End If
            If prefix2 is greater than or equal to 11:
                If prefix2 is less than or equal to 19:
                    Return PHONE_CLASS_LANDLINE
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If nat_len is greater than or equal to 3:
            Let d0b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 0
            Let d1b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 1
            Let d2b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national_str, 2
            Let prefix3 be ((d0b minus 48) multiplied by 100) plus ((d1b minus 48) multiplied by 10) plus (d2b minus 48)
            If prefix3 is equal to 500:
                Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
            End If
            If prefix3 is equal to 800:
                Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
            End If
            If prefix3 is equal to 808:
                Return PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE
            End If
        End If
        Return PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN
    End If

    Return PHONE_CLASS_UNKNOWN
End Process

@Reasoning
Predicate accessors that wrap the classification enum for ergonomic calls.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare to the corresponding enum constant.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_is_mobile" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cls be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 32
    If cls is equal to PHONE_CLASS_MOBILE:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "phone_is_landline" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cls be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 32
    If cls is equal to PHONE_CLASS_LANDLINE:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "phone_is_voip" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cls be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 32
    If cls is equal to PHONE_CLASS_VOIP:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "phone_is_toll_free" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cls be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 32
    If cls is equal to PHONE_CLASS_TOLL_FREE:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: FORMATTING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Convert an integer 0..9 to its ASCII digit character.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Add 48.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on out-of-range input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_digit_char" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    If value is greater than 9:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return value plus 48
End Process

@Reasoning
Render the phone number in E.164 form: "+<cc><national>".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
StringBuilder: '+' + integer_to_string(cc) + national.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No untrusted input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_to_e164" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 0
    Let national be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 8
    If national is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 43
    proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, cc
    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, national
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Render the phone number in international form per ITU-T E.123:
  "+<cc> <area>-<exchange>-<subscriber>"
for the US/NANP and similar groupings. For other countries fall back to
"+<cc> <national>" with the national digits emitted verbatim.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on country code. For cc==1 with national length 10: emit "+1
AAA-BBB-CCCC". For others use the generic spacer form.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No untrusted input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_to_international" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 0
    Let national be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 8
    If national is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nat_len be proc string_length from StringCore with national
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 43
    proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, cc
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
    If cc is equal to 1:
        If nat_len is equal to 10:
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than 3:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 45
            Set i to 3
            While i is less than 6:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 45
            Set i to 6
            While i is less than 10:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        Otherwise:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, national
        End If
    Otherwise:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, national
    End If
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Render the national-only display form. For NANP this is "(AAA) BBB-CCCC".
For other countries the digits are emitted as a single block (callers who
need locale-specific spacing can layer on top).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on country code. NANP: "(<3>) <3>-<4>". Others: digits-only.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No untrusted input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_to_national" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 0
    Let national be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 8
    If national is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nat_len be proc string_length from StringCore with national
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If cc is equal to 1:
        If nat_len is equal to 10:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 40
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than 3:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 41
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
            Set i to 3
            While i is less than 6:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 45
            Set i to 6
            While i is less than 10:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        Otherwise:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, national
        End If
    Otherwise:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, national
    End If
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Render the phone number as a tel: URI per RFC 3966.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
"tel:+<cc>-<national>" with hyphens separating cc from the national
number; the national number itself is emitted as digits-only because
RFC 3966 section 5.1.4 requires the global-number-digits production to
contain only digits and visual separators.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No untrusted input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "phone_to_rfc3966" takes rec as Integer returns Integer:
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 0
    Let national be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, 8
    If national is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nat_len be proc string_length from StringCore with national
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 116
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 101
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 108
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 58
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 43
    proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, cc
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 45
    If cc is equal to 1:
        If nat_len is equal to 10:
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than 3:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 45
            Set i to 3
            While i is less than 6:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 45
            Set i to 6
            While i is less than 10:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with national, i
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        Otherwise:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, national
        End If
    Otherwise:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, national
    End If
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process
